article.description: — Cole Anthony hit a hurried 3-pointer at the buzzer and the Orlando Magic stunned the Minnesota Timberwolves 97-96 on Wednesday night to stop a six-game losing streak.
article.headline: Anthony hits buzzer-beating 3, Magic edge Timberwolves 97-96
article.linkText: Anthony hits buzzer-beating 3, Magic edge Timberwolves 97-96
article.story: MINNEAPOLIS -- — In a story January 20, 2021, about the Orlando Magic-Minnesota Timberwolves game, The Associated Press erroneously stated the first name of Malik Beasley.
